The texts of 1-2 Greek prose authors are analysed and commented from linguistical and grammatical aspects. During the course selections of the works are read, translated, commented, interpreted and analysed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the works of most important Greek prose authors (Xenophon, Herodot, Pausanias, Plato etc.). The course also helps to memorize the already acquired Greek grammar, improve the abilities of syntactical analysis, to explain the backround and style of the authors and their works.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students: are able to explain the backround of the authors and texts read in the course, analyze their style, forms of dialect used in the text; analyze sentences grammatically and syntactically;  interpret the text; translate the text(s) of the read author with the help of dictionaries, grammars and internet resources; are able to find secondary sources regarding the author and text.
